es for a patient undergoing removal of the prostate and some of the surrounding tissue.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00866","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Lower Abdomen.Anesthesia. General Anesthesia\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing removal of one or both adrenal glands.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00868","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Lower Abdomen.Anesthesia. General Anesthesia\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing a renal transplant.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00870","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Lower Abdomen.Anesthesia. General Anesthesia\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing removal of a stone from the bladder.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00872","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Lower Abdomen.Anesthesia. General Anesthesia\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient partially submerged in liquid while undergoing treatment of a kidney stone or ureteral stone by extracorporeal shock wave.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00873","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Lower Abdomen.Anesthesia. General Anesthesia\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for lithotripsy extracorporeal shock wave without water bath.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00880","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Lower Abdomen.Anesthesia. General Anesthesia\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for procedures on major lower abdominal vessels not otherwise specified.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00882","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Lower Abdomen.Anesthesia. General Anesthesia\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a procedure on major lower abdominal vessels including inferior vena cava ligation.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00902","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a procedure involving the anus or rectum.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00904","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a radical (complete removal of all diseased tissue) perineal (the area around the genitali) procedure.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00906","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing vulvectomy which means excision of the external genitals of the female.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00908","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing perineal prostatectomy. In this procedure the surgical provider partially or completely removes the prostate gland by approaching it through the perineum.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00910","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing transurethral procedures including urethrocystoscopy. The surgical provider may examine the organs of the urinary system from within by inserting a special device through the urethra which is the external opening for urine outflow. This code is for procedures not specified by any other anesthesia code.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00912","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing excision of one or more tumors within the bladder performed through the urethra which is the opening for the outflow of urine.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00914","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient undergoing removal of the prostate gland through the urethra which is the opening for the outflow of urine.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"CPT","code":"00916","description":"\"Anesthesia for Procedures on the Perineum.Anesthesia. for Obstetrical Services\"","category":"Anesthesiology","procedureDetails":"\"The provider performs anesthesia services for a patient requiring bleeding control following removal of a specific tissue accessed through the urethra which is an opening for the outflow of urine.\"","version":"CPT 2026"},{"type":"HCPCS","code":"A0021","description":"Ambulance and Other Transport Services and Supplies.Ambulance services","category":"Transportation Services. medical equipment and supplies","version":"HCPS"},{"type":"HCPCS","code":"A0080","description":"Ambulance and Other Transport Services and Supplies.Ambulance services","category":"Transportation Services. medical equipment and supplies","version":"HCPS"},{"type":"HCPCS","code":"A0090","description":"Ambulance and Other Transport Services and S